Charles Richard Cathcart (November 6, 1924 – November 8, 1993) was an American Dixieland trumpet player who was best known as a member of The Lawrence Welk Show in which he appeared from 1962 to 1968.
The band from the movie stayed together in the 1950s for performances and recordings under the name Pete Kelly's Big Seven.
Cathcart also supplied music for the TV show Dragnet, which starred Jack Webb as Joe Friday.
